Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-its-like-business-class-cathay-pacific-review-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742471401000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d9743c585f1dff88b26d7f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-its-like-business-class-cathay-pacific-review-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22My%20long-haul%20flight%20in%20Cathay%20Pacific%20business%20class%20from%20Chicago%20to%20Hong%20Kong%20cost%20over%20%245%2C000.%20The%20food%2C%20drinks%2C%20and%20service%20impressed%20me.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Amber%20Gibson)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-its-like-business-class-cathay-pacific-review-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20cofounded%20Kayak%20that%20sold%20for%20%242.1%20billion.%20Here's%20how%20finding%20out%20I%20had%20bipolar%20illness%20at%2025%20impacted%20my%20career.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22938%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Paul%20English%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67dabe8d69253ccddf99ab29%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22704%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPaul%20English%20said%20he%20tried%20to%20model%20vulnerability%20as%20a%20leader%20at%20Kayak.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Paul%20English%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPaul%20English%20cofounded%20Kayak%2C%20a%20travel%20search%20engine%20that%20sold%20for%20%242.1%20billion%20in%202013.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20has%20bipolar%20disorder%20and%20has%20experienced%20manic%20and%20depressive%20episodes%20during%20his%20working%20life.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20says%20being%20vulnerable%20about%20his%20illness%20helped%20to%20create%20an%20open%20team%20culture%20at%20Kayak.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Paul%20English%2C%2061%2C%20a%20serial%20entrepreneur%20who%20founded%20the%20travel%20website%20Kayak.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftravel-budget-calculator-millennial-inflation-depressing-kayak-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKayak%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20I%20was%20around%2040%20years%20old.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20previously%20sold%20a%20company%20called%20Boston%20Light%20Software.%20One%20day%20in%202003%2C%20I%20met%20with%20another%20entrepreneur%2C%20Steve%20Hafner%2C%20through%20a%20mutual%20connection%2C%20to%20talk%20about%20a%20travel%20company%20he%20wanted%20to%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteve%20wanted%20me%20to%20come%20on%20as%20the%20CTO.%20I%20said%20would%2C%20but%20only%20as%2050%2F50%20partners.%20It%20was%20a%20bit%20arrogant%20of%20me%2C%20but%20Steve%20agreed.%20It%20was%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%2010-year%20journey.%20In%202013%2C%20Kayak%20was%20acquired%20for%20%242.1%20billion%2C%20and%20I%20left%20shortly%20afterward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYears%20before%20starting%20Kayak%2C%20I%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fbipolar-symptoms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebipolar%20illness%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%2025.%20I%20was%20going%20through%20a%20manic%20period%3A%20talking%20really%20fast%2C%20not%20sleeping%2C%20working%20through%20the%20night%20and%20having%20panic%20attacks.%20It%20was%20affecting%20my%20marriage%2C%20so%20I%20went%20to%20a%20doctor%20and%20got%20a%20diagnosis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20a%20label%20was%20a%20tremendous%20relief.%20I%20read%20everything%20I%20could%20about%20bipolar%20illness%2C%20but%20hid%20my%20diagnosis%20for%20over%20a%20decade.%20I%20was%20fearful%20people%20would%20find%20me%20crazy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20eventually%20told%20a%20few%20trusted%20people%2C%20which%20helped%20me%20feel%20less%20burdened.%20By%20the%20time%20I%20started%20Kayak%2C%20I'd%20learned%20to%20be%20more%20open%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20bipolar%20illness%20affected%20my%20time%20at%20Kayak.%20I%20was%20sometimes%20reckless%20with%20decisions%20and%20sometimes%20overwhelmed%20my%20team.%20However%2C%20I%20think%20my%20vulnerability%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommitted-white-collar-crime-bipolar-manic-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eliving%20with%20bipolar%20illness%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20helped%20me%20to%20build%20a%20team%20culture%20where%20people%20could%20be%20open%20about%20their%20struggles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2238154ba7-152b-4a4f-946a-4993ed47c302%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBuilding%20a%20great%20team%20was%20my%20No.1%20priority%20at%20Kayak%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20I%20agreed%20to%20start%20Kayak%20with%20Steve%20back%20in%20the%20early%202000s%2C%20I%20went%20home%20and%20played%20around%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fhow-to-find-your-itinerary-on-expedia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EExpedia's%20website%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20about%2015%20minutes.%20I'm%20embarrassed%20I%20did%20so%20little%20market%20research%2C%20but%20I%20felt%20confident%20I%20could%20design%20a%20simpler%2C%20faster%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUpon%20reflection%2C%20this%20confidence%20was%20probably%20a%20combination%20of%20my%20faith%20in%20my%20design%20chops%20plus%20some%20grandiosity%20that%20comes%20with%20bipolar%20illness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20career%20as%20an%20entrepreneur%2C%20I%20always%20operate%20on%20a%20team-first%2C%20customer-second%2C%20and%20profit-third%20basis.%20Magical%20teams%20build%20magical%20products%2C%20and%20magical%20products%20build%20magical%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fincome-statement%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprofit%20and%20loss%20sheets%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Kayak%2C%20I%20hired%20people%20who%20were%20fast%2C%20smart%2C%20and%20had%20good%20team%20skills.%20I%20brought%20on%20the%20four%20best%20engineers%20I'd%20worked%20with%20and%20asked%20them%20to%20bring%20in%20who%20they%20thought%20were%20the%20best.%20If%20we%20hired%20someone%20who%20was%20rough%20on%20other%20people%20and%20caused%20stress%2C%20we'd%20fire%20them%20if%20we%20couldn't%20cure%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20also%20extremely%20customer-focused%20at%20Kayak.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20took%20most%20of%20the%20customer%20support%20calls%20myself%20for%20the%20first%20year.%20Then%2C%20I%20got%20our%20engineers%20to%20do%20customer%20service%20%E2%80%94%20engineers%20became%20very%20motivated%20to%20fix%20problems%2C%20and%20customers%20were%20blown%20away%20by%20getting%20replies%20straight%20from%20the%20engineers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220c94eb0b-caed-4851-9487-6bbfcf5e5cfa%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20sold%20Kayak%20for%20%242.1%20billion%20in%202013%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20took%20Kayak%20public%20in%202012.%20We'd%20become%20very%20profitable%20and%20felt%20confident%20in%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20agreed%20on%20a%20deal%20with%20Priceline%20that%20year.%20They%20acquired%20Kayak%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2FArchives%2Fedgar%2Fdata%2F1075531%2F000107553113000045%2Fpcln6301310q.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%242.1%20billion%20in%202013%3C%2Fa%3E%20based%20on%20the%20purchase%20value%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20stayed%20at%20Kayak%20for%20several%20months%2C%20but%20I%20wanted%20to%20try%20something%20new%2C%20so%20I%20stepped%20down%20as%20Kayak's%20CTO%20in%20December%202013.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cb15778f-235e-4c7a-acfe-0d1a46410744%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHaving%20bipolar%20illness%20has%20its%20good%20and%20bad%20sides.%20I%20learned%20how%20to%20live%20with%20both%20at%20Kayak.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20open%20about%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmental-health-school-days-unexcused-illinois-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emental%20health%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20working%20at%20Kayak.%20I%20would%20email%20the%20company%20during%20Mental%20Illness%20Awareness%20Week%2C%20tell%20them%20a%20bit%20about%20living%20with%20bipolar%20illness%2C%20and%20let%20people%20know%20they%20can%20talk%20to%20me%20if%20they're%20struggling.%20I'd%20always%20get%20floods%20of%20appreciative%20emails%20back%20in%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBipolar%20illness%20had%20a%20big%20impact%20on%20how%20I%20showed%20up%20at%20work.%20During%20depressive%20days%2C%20I%20couldn't%20get%20out%20of%20bed.%20But%20during%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbipolar-therapist-excerpt-stigma-inpatient-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanic%20episodes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20was%20wild%20and%20reckless%20about%20wanting%20to%20try%20different%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hypomania%20that%20comes%20with%20bipolar%20illness%20gives%20you%20a%20sense%20of%20grandiosity%20and%20confidence%2C%20which%20can%20be%20good%20when%20you're%20trying%20to%20do%20something%20new.%20At%20Kayak%2C%20I'd%20get%20new%20ideas%20every%20day%20and%20come%20to%20the%20team%20with%20suggestions%2C%20but%20the%20team%20felt%20they%20couldn't%20handle%20all%20those%20ideas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20senior%20VP%20started%20telling%20engineers%20not%20to%20do%20anything%20I%20asked%20them%20unless%20I%20asked%20them%20twice.%20When%20I%20found%20out%20years%20later%2C%20I%20was%20sad%20at%20first%2C%20but%20I%20can%20see%20that%20it%20was%20a%20good%20idea%20in%20hindsight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20upsides.%20I've%20made%20some%20incredible%20friends%20through%20the%20Bipolar%20Social%20Club%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20I%20started%20in%202023.%20It's%20helpful%20talking%20to%20people%20with%20similar%20experiences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20learned%2C%20even%20during%20the%20Kayak%20years%2C%20how%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20the%20good%20parts%20of%20bipolar%20and%20manage%20the%20bad%20parts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20Kayak%20would%20have%20taken%20longer%20and%20may%20not%20have%20been%20as%20successful%20had%20I%20not%20had%20bipolar%20illness.%20Because%20of%20the%20enormous%20energy%20and%20grandiosity%20I%20had%20at%20Kayak%2C%20people%20would%20see%20my%20drive%20and%20how%20hard%20I%20worked%2C%20which%20led%20them%20to%20work%20hard%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20often%20said%20people%20follow%20confidence%20but%20are%20loyal%20to%20vulnerability%2C%20and%20I%20try%20to%20be%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20very%20confident%20in%20some%20aspects%20of%20my%20life%2C%20like%20my%20product%20design%20capabilities%2C%20but%20I%20also%20try%20to%20expose%20my%20weaknesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20people%20have%20followed%20my%20confidence%20but%20have%20also%20felt%20comfortable%20asking%20me%20for%20support%20if%2C%20for%20example%2C%20they%20struggled%20to%20focus%20on%20coding%20because%20they%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flate-adhd-diagnosis-relief-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EADHD%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20created%20a%20place%20where%20people%20worked%20really%20hard%20but%20would%20also%20be%20open%20about%20their%20struggles%20in%20private%20conversations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20mental%20health%20in%20the%20workplace%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Accheong%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eccheong%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkayak-founder-paul-english-bipolar-illness-leadership-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22