d%20after%20Elon%20Musk-owned%20social%20media%20giant%20X%20sued%20the%20Centre%2C%20accusing%20it%20of%20misusing%20Information%20Technology%20laws%20to%20create%20an%20%26quot%3Bunlawful%20blocking%20regime%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BProcess%20will%20be%20followed%20and%20social%20media%20platforms%20should%20follow%20the%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20source%20has%20told%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20sharp%20response%20comes%20after%20X%2C%20previously%20known%20as%20Twitter%2C%20filed%20a%20writ%20petition%20against%20the%20Centre%20and%20its%20ministries%20in%20the%20Karnataka%20High%20Court.%20In%20its%20petition%2C%20X%20has%20cited%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20verdict%20in%20the%202015%20Shreya%20Singhal%20case%2C%20which%20struck%20down%20Section%2066A%20of%20the%20Indian%20Information%20Technology%20Act%20that%20criminalised%20sending%20offensive%20messages%20on%20communication%20devices.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EX's%20petition%20says%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Electronics%20and%20Information%20Technology%20has%20told%20central%20ministries%20and%20state%20governments%20and%20%26quot%3Beffectively%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20local%20police%20officers%26quot%3B%20that%20they%20are%20authorised%20to%20issue%20information%20blocking%20orders%20under%20Section%2079(3)(b)%2C%20outside%20the%20Section%2069A%20process.%C2%A0Section%2079(3)(b)%20lays%20down%20that%20an%20IT%20intermediary%20loses%20its%20immunity%20from%20liability%20if%20it%20does%20not%20%26quot%3Bexpeditiously%20remove%20or%20disable%20access%26quot%3B%20to%20material%20flagged%20by%20a%20government%20agency%20as%20linked%20to%20an%20unlawful%20act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EX's%20petition%20says%20that%20the%20use%20of%20Section%2079(3)(b)%20circumvents%20Section%2069A%2C%20which%20empowers%20the%20government%20to%20issue%20directions%20to%20block%20public%20access%20to%20information%20but%20lays%20down%20safeguards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSection%2079%20merely%20exempts%20intermediaries%20from%20liability%20for%20third-party%20content%3B%20it%20does%20not%20empower%20the%20government%20to%20issue%20information%20blocking%20orders%20in%20violation%20of%20Section%2069A.%20A%20full%2023%20years%20after%20Section%2079%20was%20enacted%2C%20and%2014%20years%20after%20the%20current%20version%20went%20into%20effect%2C%20Respondents%20are%20now%20attempting%20to%20misuse%20Section%2079%20to%20create%20an%20unlawful%20blocking%20regime%20without%20any%20of%20the%20protections%20that%20exist%20under%20Section%2069A%2C%20the%20Blocking%20Rules%2C%20and%20the%20law%20laid%20down%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20Shreya%20Singhal%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20petition%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20petition%2C%20X%20said%20the%20Centre%20is%20%26quot%3Battempting%20to%20bypass%20the%20multiple%20procedural%20safeguards%20in%20the%20Blocking%20Rules%20and%20the%20specified%20grounds%20of%20Section%2069A%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20it%20violates%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20said%20the%20Centre%20and%20the%20other%20respondents%20have%20lawful%20avenues%20to%20block%20information%20in%20an%20emergency.%20%26quot%3BAny%20government%20agency%20can%20use%20the%20Section%2069A%20process%20by%20sending%20a%20request%20to%20the%20Designated%20Officer%20under%20Section%2069A.%20Under%20Rules%204%20to%206%20of%20the%20Blocking%20Rules%2C%20central%20and%20state%20agencies%20have%20nodal%20officers%20who%20send%20blocking%20requests%20to%20the%20Designated%20Officer.%20Any%20person%20can%20approach%20a%20nodal%20officer%2C%20who%20forwards%20the%20request%20for%20blocking%20to%20the%20Designated%20Officer%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EX%20has%20said%20the%20Centre's%20actions%20threaten%20its%20business%20model%20that%20rests%20on%20people%20sharing%20lawful%20information.%20%26quot%3BThe%20X%20platform%20derives%20value%20and%20revenue%20from%20its%20user%20base%20and%20the%20lawful%20content%20they%20generate.%20Thus%2C%20unlawful%20or%20unjustified%20information%20blocking%20orders%20cause%20harm%20to%20X%20and%20its%20ability%20to%20operate.%20Respondents'%20ultra%20vires%20actions%20of%20issuing%20information%20blocking%20orders%2C%20without%20following%20due%20process%20of%20law%2C%20aggrieve%20X%20by%20violating%20X's%20Article%2014%20rights%20and%20detrimentally%20impacting%20its%20business.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government's%20counter%2C%20according%20to%20sources%2C%20is%20that%C2%A0Section%2079(3)(b)%20of%20the%20IT%20Act%20empowers%20it%20to%20notify%20intermediaries%20like%20X%20to%20remove%20unlawful%20content%20quickly%20and%20effectively.%20The%20sources%20added%20that%C2%A0Section%2079(3)(b)%20is%20not%20dependent%20on%20Section%2069A's%20blocking%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742469420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2F81vll5j_elon-musk-x-_625x300_20_March_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhave-to-follow-law-government-sources-on-xs-lawsuit-against-centre-7967751%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20government%20will%20follow%20due%20process%20and%20social%20media%20platforms%20must%20follow%20the%20law%2C%20sources%20have%20said%20after%20Elon%20Musk-owned%20social%20media%20giant%20X%20sued%20the%20Centre%2C%20accusing%20it%20of%20misusing%20Information%20Technology%20laws%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhave-to-follow-law-government-sources-on-xs-lawsuit-against-centre-7967751%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kangana%20on%20groupism%2C%20bullying%20in%20B'wood%3A%20If%20I%20do%20anything...%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742469383000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-119255374%2Cimgsize-41960.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fn