2%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fchina-has-executed-four-canadians-13332340%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fchina-has-executed-four-canadians-13332340%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fchina-has-executed-four-canadians-13332340%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Severance%3A%20Are%20You%20An%20'Innie'%20Or%20An%20'Outie'%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ENobody%20would've%20expected%20%3Cem%3ESeverance%20%3C%2Fem%3Eto%20become%20the%20kind%20of%20pop-culture%20phenomenon%20it%20is%20today.%20Back%20in%202022%2C%20when%20the%20show%20premiered%20on%20AppleTV%2B%2C%20it%20was%20met%20with%20barely%20a%20whimper.%20But%20why%20is%20the%20series%2C%20critiquing%20worker%20exploitation%20and%20corporate%20greed%2C%20getting%20such%20rave%20reviews%20three%20years%20after%20its%20first%20season%20appeared%3F%20What%20gives%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20its%20popularity%20is%20a%20sign%20of%20our%20times.%20Maybe%20all%20of%20us%20are%20so%20sick%20and%20tired%20of%20our%20jobs%20that%20a%20science-fiction%20show%20about%20a%20larger-than-life%20corporate%20entity%20psychologically%20abusing%20its%20employees%20hits%20too%20close%20to%20home.%20Or%20perhaps%20being%20severed'%20seems%20strangely%20appealing%20to%20some%20of%20us%20so%20that%20our%20workplace%20trauma%20doesn't%20spill%20into%20our%20personal%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFans%20have%20been%20writing%20lengthy%20threads%20dissecting%20the%20visual%20cues%20in%20%3Cem%3ESeverance%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Conspiracy%20theorists%20have%20put%20on%20their%20tin%20foil%20hats%20and%20made%20intelligent%20guesses%20about%20the%20unfolding%20mystery%2C%20which%20culminates%20in%20the%20season%20finale%20releasing%20on%20March%2021.%20%3Cem%3ESeverance%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20to%20the%202020s%20what%20%3Cem%3EGame%20of%20Thrones%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20to%20the%20previous%20decade.%20Theme%20parties%2C%20cosplays%2C%20fan%20edits%20and%20podcasts%20analysing%20the%20plot%20twists%20are%20proof%20that%20Ben%20Stiller's%20show%20will%20go%20down%20as%20one%20of%20the%20greatest%20in%20pop-culture%20history.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20the%20reason%20the%20show%20resonates%20so%20much%20with%20viewers%20today%20is%20because%20it%20exposes%20the%20sinister%20nature%20of%20corporate%20drudgery%20while%20simultaneously%20urging%20them%20to%20be%20the%20champions%20of%20an%20inevitable%20work%20revolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%20Them%20Rebel%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20no%20surprise%20that%20the%20most%20rebellious%20employee%20on%20the%20severed%20floor%2C%20Helly%20R%20(played%20by%20a%20phenomenal%20Britt%20Lower)%2C%20got%20the%20loudest%20cheers%20and%20hoots%20when%20she%20locked%20horns%20with%20her%20boss%2C%20Seth%20Milchick%20(Tramell%20Tillman)%20in%20last%20week's%20episode.%20But%20she's%20not%20the%20only%20rebel%20on%20the%20floor.%20At%20one%20point%2C%20Milchick%20himself%20asks%20Mr%20Drummond%E2%80%94who%20had%20earlier%20been%20critical%20of%20his%20usage%20of%20big%20words%E2%80%94to%20%26quot%3Bdevour%20flatulence%26quot%3B%2C%20or%2C%20to%20be%20clearer%2C%20%26quot%3Beat%20shit%26quot%3B.%20The%20moment%20even%20inspired%20yours%20truly%20to%20go%20on%20LinkedIn%20and%20call%20out%20their%20toxic%20boss.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20scene%20from%20the%20same%20episode%2C%20Milchick%20calls%20up%20Mark%2C%20who%20is%20reintegrating%20and%20trying%20to%20free%20his%20wife%2C%20Gemma%2C%20from%20the%20Lumon%20building.%20At%20first%2C%20Mark%20lies%20about%20being%20sick.%20But%20then%2C%20he%20quickly%20backtracks%20and%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20not%20sick%E2%80%94I%20just%20need%20the%20day.%20You%20know%2C%20life%20stuff%26quot%3B.%20The%20moment%20is%20monumental%20in%20TV%20history%20for%20multiple%20reasons.%20Not%20only%20did%20Mark%20S%20stand%20up%20for%20himself%20and%20risk%20being%20locked%20out%20of%20the%20Lumon%20building%2C%20but%20he%2C%20unknowingly%2C%20inspired%20Milchick%20to%20rebel%20too.%20In%20a%20scene%2C%20Milchick%20tears%20up%20realising%20Lumon%20promised%20him%20work-life%20balance.%20Much%20like%20his%20subordinate%2C%20Milchick%2C%20too%2C%20is%20consumed%20by%20work.%20He%20has%20been%20loyal%20to%20Lumon%20all%20these%20years%2C%20only%20for%20him%20to%20find%20a%20cathartic%20release%20in%20Mark-Helly's%20anti-work%20rhetoric.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20Own%20Nothing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20to%20the%20dismay%20of%20%3Cem%3ESeverance%20%3C%2Fem%3Efans%2C%20Episode%208%20focused%20entirely%20on%20Ms%20Cobel%20(Patricia%20Arquette)%2C%20the%20ex-floor%20manager%20at%20Lumon%20who%20has%20lived%20a%20difficult%20life%20herself.%20Fans%20were%20still%20on%20a%20sun-induced%20high%20from%20last%20week's%20episode%20Chikhai%20Bardo'%2C%20so%20the%20stunning%20revelations%20in%20episode%208%20flew%20under%20the%20radar.%20A%20lesser-appreciated%20reveal%20in%20the%20episode%20focused%20on%20how%20Ms%20Cobel%20not%20only%20worked%20for%20Lumon%20as%20a%20child%20(the%20legal%20violation%20of%20it%20all!)%20and%20on%20how%20she%20had%20also%20designed%20the%20severance%20chip%20but%20wasn't%20given%20credit%20for%20it%20because%20%26quot%3BKier%20said%20knowledge%20is%20for%20all.%20That%20if%20I%20sought%20credit%2C%20I%20would%20be%20banished%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20sad%20reminder%20for%20all%20kinds%20of%20creators%20working%20across%20industries%E2%80%94whatever%20intellectual%20property%20we%20create%20for%20a%20company%20is%20owned%20by%20it.%20Ms%20Cobel%20realises%20much%20later%20that%20the%20Eagens%20exploited%20her%20intellectual%20capabilities%20for%20their%20sick%2C%20twisted%20experiment.%20But%20she%20isn't%20the%20only%20child%20Lumon%20exploits%20for%20labour.%20In%20the%20ninth%20episode%2C%20we%20see%20a%20young%20receptionist%2C%20Ms%20Huang%20(Sarah%20Bock)%2C%20enter%20a%20bus%20(presumably%20meant%20for%20kids)%20and%20leave%20the%20Lumon%20building%20after%20completing%20her%20winter%20fellowship%2C%20pointing%20to%20a%20possible%20network%20of%20underage%20employees%20working%20at%20apprentice%20shops.%20Such%20is%20the%20corrosive%20nature%20of%20corporate%20greed%20that%20it%20may%20not%20spare%20even%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20You%20Speak%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESeverance%20%3C%2Fem%3Ealso%20touches%20on%20the%20realities%20of%20race.%20It%20consciously%20and%20very%20clearly%20demarcates%20employees%20who%20are%20brainwashed%20and%20would%20do%20just%20about%20anything%20to%20support%20Lumon%2FEagans%2C%20from%20the%20rebels.%20Case%20in%20point%3A%20Seth%20Milchick.%20Milchick%20is%20indeed%20a%20black%20man%20in%20a%20white%20man's%20world.%20While%20the%20success%20of%20the%20MDR%20department%20depends%20solely%20on%20Mark's%20number-refining%2C%20Milchick%20is%20tasked%20with%20the%20responsibility%20of%20making%20sure%20none%20of%20his%20predominantly%20white%20innies%20stray%20from%20Kier's%20path%20and%20finish%20the%20tasks%20to%20their%20completion.%20For%20many%2C%20Stiller's%20gaze%20on%20people%20of%20colour%20is%20problematic.%20This%20couldn't%20be%20further%20from%20the%20truth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnlike%20Mark%20and%20Helly%2C%20the%20white%2C%20rebellious%20innies%20of%20the%20MDR%20department%2C%20Milchick%20cannot%20afford%20to%20raise%20his%20voice%20against%20the%20Eagens%2FKiers%20owing%20to%20his%20racial%20identity%2C%20the%20same%20way%20a%20white%20employee%20might%20find%20it%20easier%20to%20call%20out%20their%20white%20boss%20at%20the%20workplace%20than%20a%20black%20employee.%20It%20is%20no%20surprise%20that%20Gemma%2C%20a%20woman%20of%20colour%2C%20is%20not%20only%20denied%20her%20bodily%20autonomy%20but%20suffers%20the%20most%20out%20of%20all%20the%20female%20characters%20in%20the%20show.%20On%20the%20surface%2C%20it%20might%20seem%20that%20all%20the%20faces%20of%20the%20'Severance%20Reform'%20are%20white%20men%20and%20women%2C%20but%20a%20closer%20look%20reveals%20that%20the%20gender%20and%20racial%20identities%20of%20Lumon's%20employees%20decide%20who%20gets%20to%20rebel%2C%20and%20how%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPerhaps%20The%20World%20Ends%20Here%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESeverance%20%3C%2Fem%3Eisn't%20just%20a%20genre-defying%20sci-fi%20mystery%20drama%20that%20makes%20you%20want%20to%20nerd%20out.%20At%20its%20core%2C%20it%20urges%20us%20to%20question%20the%20corporations%20that%20are%20slowly%20taking%20over%20our%20lives%20bit%20by%20bit%2C%20leaving%20us%20with%20barely%20any%20space%20to%20breathe.%20Being%20able%20to%20afford%20to%20take%20the%20elevator%20itself%20might%20soon%20feel%20like%20a%20privilege%20in%20India%2C%20what%20with%20industrialists%20asking%20their%20employees%20to%20work%2070%2C%2090%20hours%20a%20week%20now.%20Perhaps%20the%20employees%20can%20just%20take%20a%20leaf%20out%20of%20Gemma's%20(Dichen%20Lachman)%20book%20and%20stay%20in%20the%20office%20building%20forever.%20The%20work%20won't%20end%2C%20and%20neither%20will%20capitalist%20greed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20much%20of%20%3Cem%3ESeverance%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20science%20fiction%2C%20and%20how%20much%20of%20it%20is%20already%20a%20reality%3F%20Sure%2C%20a%20corporate%20entity%20like%20Lumon%20building%20entire%20towns%20to%20control%20workers%20and%20their%20families%20may%20be%20hard%20to%20imagine%20in%20the%20real%20world.%20Or%2C%20is%20it%3F%20Given%20how%20tightly%20all%20of%20our%20paychecks%E2%80%94and%20therefore%2C%20survival%E2%80%94are%20controlled%20by%20the%20elite%2C%20is%20%3Cem%3ESeverance's%20%3C%2Fem%3Edystopian%20world%20really%20that%20fantastical%3F%20Or%20is%20it%20already%20here%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThink%20about%20it.%20But%20don't%20forget%20to%20log%20in%20on%20time%E2%80%94and%20praise%20your%2