the%20very%20beginning%2C%20we%20taught%20our%20son%20about%20money.%20At%20a%20young%20age%2C%20we%20gave%20him%20an%20allowance.%20It%20was%20his%20to%20spend%20any%20way%20he%20chose.%20When%20he%20wanted%20something%20like%20a%20video%20game%2C%20he%20needed%20to%20spend%20his%20money.%20If%20we%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcomparing-legoland-us-parks-california-florida-new-york-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewent%20somewhere%20special%20like%20Legoland%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20would%20offer%20to%20get%20him%20something%20up%20to%20%2420%2C%20but%20anything%20else%20came%20from%20his%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20when%20we%20fell%20on%20hard%20financial%20times%20we%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillionaire-parent-teaches-kids-budgeting-entitlement-stability-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincluded%20our%20son%20in%20the%20discussion%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20affected%20all%20of%20us.%20We%20would%20talk%20about%20money%20and%20what%20we%20had%20to%20spend%20each%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20always%20been%20somewhat%20frugal%20with%20money.%20Still%2C%20we%20did%20all%20the%20normal%20cost%20cutting.%20Vacation%20travel%20was%20out.%20We%20cut%20our%20premium%20cable%20channels%2C%20and%20stopped%20eating%20out%20as%20much.%20Instead%20of%20a%20big%20trip%2C%20we%20took%20our%20little%20camping%20trailer%20on%20local%20trips.%20Hiking%20and%20museums%20replaced%20amusement%20parks%20and%20movie%20theaters.%20Date%20night%20was%20dinner%20at%20home%2C%20followed%20by%20a%20rented%20video.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227f90fddc-6169-4a03-aafa-8d392572bbcd%5C%22%3EI%20started%20selling%20collectibles%20on%20eBay%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20began%20getting%20the%20house%20ready%20to%20sell.%20We%20knew%20it'd%20be%20better%20to%20sell%20it%20if%20we%20could%20rather%20than%20have%20the%20bank%20take%20it%2C%20but%20the%20house%20was%20not%20in%20any%20condition%20to%20put%20on%20the%20market.%20We%20started%20with%20a%20general%20purge%20of%20old%20furniture%2C%20clothes%2C%20toys%2C%20and%20household%20stuff.%20Anything%20that%20didn't%20have%20garage%20sale%20value%20went%20to%20Goodwill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20lots%20of%20antiques%20and%20collectibles.%20Some%20I%20inherited%20from%20my%20mom%2C%20but%20we%20also%20had%20souvenirs%20from%20our%20trips%20to%20Disney%20and%20NASA%20collectibles.%20I%20hated%20to%20part%20with%20them%2C%20but%20they%20were%20just%20things%2C%20and%20we%20needed%20the%20money.%20So%2C%20they%20had%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20small%20studio%20on%20the%20dining%20room%20table%20for%20listing%20our%20hobby%20items%20online%2C%20and%20we%20set%20up%20an%20eBay%20store.%20We%20got%20dozens%20of%20boxes%20from%20the%20attic%20and%20sorted%20them.%20We%20set%20up%20tables%20in%20the%20living%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEverything%20was%20photographed%2C%20priced%2C%20and%20listed.%20We%20packed%20items%20up%20when%20things%20sold%20and%20made%20daily%20trips%20to%20the%20post%20office%20and%20UPS%20store.%20My%20son%20even%20helped%20with%20the%20packing%20and%20shipping.%20The%20money%20kept%20us%20going.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a2d821af-5782-409c-b131-d1ed209a4600%5C%22%3EMy%20son%20got%20a%20job%20to%20help%20us%20pay%20bills%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20son%2C%20just%2014%2C%20got%20a%20summer%20job%20at%20the%20Boy%20Scout%20camp%20in%20San%20Diego.%20He'd%20wanted%20to%20do%20it%20but%20had%20previously%20been%20too%20young.%20My%20wife%20spent%20that%20summer%20alone%20managing%20our%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%20in%20his%20life%2C%20my%20son%20confided%20in%20me%20that%20he%20worked%20at%20the%20scout%20camp%20all%20those%20summers%20to%20bring%20in%20some%20money%20and%20help%20us%20save%20by%20not%20having%20to%20feed%20him%20during%20those%20months.%20Though%20we%20were%20never%20at%20a%20point%20where%20we%20couldn't%20put%20food%20on%20the%20table%2C%20it%20was%20difficult%20to%20